Barcelona have announced their squad that will take on Borussia Dortmund in the UEFA Champions League group-stage fixture on Tuesday night at Westfalenstadion. Barcelona coach, Ernesto Valverde named a 22-man squad to face Dortmund on Monday through the club’s official website. Captain Lionel Messi was included in the squad, after he missed Barcelona’s La Liga 5-2 victory against Valencia over the weekend, while Dembélé and Umtiti will miss Tuesday’s clash due to injury. Below is Barcelona’s squad against Dortmund: Ter Stegen, N. Semedo, Piqué, I. Rakitic, Sergio, Todibo, Arthur, Suárez, Messi, Neto, Lenglet, M. Wague, Griezmann, Jordi Alba, Aleñá, S. Roberto, F. De Jong, Vidal, Junior, Iñaki Peña, C. Pérez and Ansu Fati. The kick-off time for the match is 8pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.